{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "dra:lamentations.5",
    "translationId": "dra",
    "bookSlug": "lamentations",
    "chapterNumber": 5,
    "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 5",
    "summary": "Source text for Lamentations 5 in Douay-Rheims Bible (Challoner)."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "dra:lamentations.5.1",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 5:1",
      "text": "Remember, O Lord, what is come upon us: consider and behold our reproach.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:lamentations.5.2",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 5:2",
      "text": "Our inheritance is turned to aliens: our houses to strangers.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:lamentations.5.3",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 5:3",
      "text": "We are become orphans without a father: our mothers are as widows.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:lamentations.5.4",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 5:4",
      "text": "We have drunk our water for money: we have bought our wood.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:lamentations.5.5",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 5:5",
      "text": "We were dragged by the necks, we were weary and no rest was given us.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:lamentations.5.6",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 5:6",
      "text": "We have given our hand to Egypt, and to the Assyrians, that we might be satisfied with bread.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:lamentations.5.7",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 5:7",
      "text": "Our fathers have sinned, and are not: and we have borne their iniquities.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:lamentations.5.8",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 5:8",
      "text": "Servants have ruled over us: there was none to redeem us out of their hand.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:lamentations.5.9",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 5:9",
      "text": "We fetched our bread at the peril of our lives, because of the sword in the desert.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:lamentations.5.10",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 5:10",
      "text": "Our skin was burnt as an oven, by reason of the violence of the famine.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:lamentations.5.11",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 5:11",
      "text": "They oppressed the women in Sion, and the virgins in the cities of Juda.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:lamentations.5.12",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 5:12",
      "text": "The princes were hanged up by their hand: they did not respect the persons of the ancients.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:lamentations.5.13",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 5:13",
      "text": "They abused the young men indecently: and the children fell under the wood.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:lamentations.5.14",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 5:14",
      "text": "The ancients have ceased from the gates: the young men from the choir of the singers.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:lamentations.5.15",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 5:15",
      "text": "The joy of our heart is ceased, our dancing is turned into mourning.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:lamentations.5.16",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 5:16",
      "text": "The crown is fallen from our head: woe to us, because we have sinned.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:lamentations.5.17",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 5:17",
      "text": "Therefore is our heart sorrowful, therefore are our eyes become dim.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:lamentations.5.18",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 5:18",
      "text": "For mount Sion, because it is destroyed, foxes have walked upon it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:lamentations.5.19",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 5:19",
      "text": "But thou, O Lord, shalt remain for ever, thy throne from generation to generation.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:lamentations.5.20",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 5:20",
      "text": "Why wilt thou forget us for ever? why wilt thou forsake us for a long time?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:lamentations.5.21",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 5:21",
      "text": "Convert us, O Lord, to thee, and we shall be converted: renew our days, as from the beginning.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:lamentations.5.22",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "lamentations",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Lamentations 5:22",
      "text": "But thou hast utterly rejected us, thou art exceedingly angry with us.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
